Residents in targeted parts of Johannesburg will not have water overnight on an indefinite basis as the city takes drastic action to reduce consumption.Johannesburg Water put out an alert late Thursday saying that some reservoir outlet valves would be closed resulting in no water supply at all in places between 8pm and 4am until further notice . The targeted water restrictions are aimed at reducing escalating water consumption despite the recent rainfall which led to a slight increase in dam levels.Check your suburb here: https://www.johannesburgwater.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/TARGERTED-WATER-RESTRICTIONS-PLAN-January-2017.pdfWere you affected overnight? How are you managing? Please share your views with us in the comments section of our social media platforms on Facebook and Twitter. 